Alternate data formats


Another format you are likely to encounter for tandem mass spectrometry data is 
Mascot Generic Format
 or 
mgf
.  Mascot Generic Format (
mgf
) is the data file format preferred by the 
Mascot
 search engine.  It is a text based format is much easier to read by hand than the 
mzML
 file.  Each spectrum appears between "BEGIN IONS" and "END IONS" statements and simply consists of (
mz
,
intensity
) pairs.  Additional summary information about the precursor (whole peptide) ion such as its mass, retention time and charge are included. 






